Scope / licensing
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The Apache-2.0 license covers the original work of this project:
  - rtl/core/*               (the RV32 core IP — the deliverable)
  - fw/*                     (optional example bring-up firmware)
  - sim/* (except sim/embench/), tb/*   (test harnesses)
  - tests/*                  (directed tests)
  - docs/*, vivado/*         (documentation and build scripts)

EXCEPTION — sim/embench/ is licensed GPL-3.0-or-later (see the SPDX headers in
those files). The Embench-IoT board port builds against Embench-IoT (GPL-3.0),
so the port files are marked GPLv3 to match. It is an OPTIONAL
performance-measurement harness and is NOT part of the core IP deliverable
(rtl/core/*), which remains Apache-2.0 and carries no GPL obligation.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party benchmarks (fetched at build time — NOT redistributed here)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  - CoreMark(R) is an EEMBC benchmark; its source is cloned from
    github.com/eembc/coremark when you run `make coremark`. The committed
    sim/coremark/* files are an ORIGINAL bare-metal port (Apache-2.0); no EEMBC
    source is vendored in this repository.
  - Embench-IoT (github.com/embench/embench-iot, GPL-3.0) is likewise fetched
    when you run `make embench`; the committed sim/embench/* board-port files
    are GPL-3.0-or-later (see above).
